## Description
The **Track Documents **task allows to enable the integration with the Doxee Platform 2 Tracking &amp; Reporting system service, by processing 400/410 events and forwarding the corresponding 552/562 events to T&amp;R.

> Note

For more information, see:

- [Tracking and Reporting User Manual](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Tracking%2Band%2BReporting%2BUser%2BManual) 

- [TR 4XX-5XX: Mapping](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/TR%2B4XX-5XX%3A%2BMapping)

This task may be placed after a [Compose Documents (DC)](/doxee-platform/docs/compose-documents-dc-batch-workflow-task-reference) task or after a custom [Process Files](/doxee-platform/docs/process-files-batch-workflow-task-reference) task that generates the required 400/410 events. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Important

You must enable the **Analytics **option at workflow level for the integration to work. For more information, see: [How to Configure a Batch /On-Demand Workflow to Use Tracking &amp; Reporting](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=134546647).

> Important

If multiple jobs are launched using the same work unit, the events corresponding to the older job(s) will be automatically removed from the T&amp;R DP2 UI, in favor of the events corresponding to the latest job. The work unit reception date, on the other hand, will correspond to the first job that was executed.

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Site **field, select the instance from which to retrieve the Staging &amp; Aggregation configurations.

> Note

Each tenant is associated with a site. A site may be associated with one or more tenants.

The endpoint used to access the S&amp;A system is: *&lt;site endpoint&gt;/&lt;portal path&gt;/sa/&lt;operation path&gt;*.

- In the **Input &gt; Source component **field, select the task from which to retrieve the required 400/410 files for generating 552 and 562 files.

> Note

For more information, see:

[TR 4XX-5XX: Mapping](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/TR%2B4XX-5XX%3A%2BMapping)

[TR 400H - Digital Document Production - 00552 Header](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/TR%2B400H%2B-%2BDigital%2BDocument%2BProduction%2B-%2B00552%2BHeader) 

- [TR 400D - Digital Document Production - 00552 Detail](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/TR%2B400D%2B-%2BDigital%2BDocument%2BProduction%2B-%2B00552%2BDetail) 

- [TR 410H - Digital Document Production - 00562 Header](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/TR%2B410H%2B-%2BDigital%2BDocument%2BProduction%2B-%2B00562%2BHeader) 

- [TR 410D - Digital Document Production - 00562 Detail](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/TR%2B410D%2B-%2BDigital%2BDocument%2BProduction%2B-%2B00562%2BDetail)

- In the **Context **section, select the required parameters, which must match the configuration of the Tracking &amp; Reporting process on Doxee Platform 2:

**Distribution channel**

- **Media format**

- **Delivery product**
